## Signatory Guidelines {#signatory-guidelines}

From time to time you may need to engage a service provider, partner, or other vendor in the course of your work. All of these types of relationships should be made under a written contract. All such contracts must be prepared or reviewed by the Uniswap Labs legal team.

Contracts may only be signed by an executive (i.e., CEO, CLO, or COO) or by someone else who has been given express authority by the board of directors to sign agreements for the Company or one-off authorization by the CLO. If you have questions, you should check with your manager or the legal team about the appropriate signatory for a contract.

